steps.name: the latest version of CDISC has Version Label: "2020-06-26 Release" and Version Number: "65.0.0"
I am signed in successfully as "Community Reader"
I am on Dashboard
I click "Browse every version of CDISC CT"
I see CDISC Terminology History page is displayed
the latest release version is as specified in pre-condition
I click Context menu for "2019-06-28"
I verify that Show and Search are enabled and all other menus are disabled for "2019-06-28"
I click "Show" in context menu for "2019-06-28" on the History page
I see the list of code lists for the "2019-06-28 Release"
the release has 891 entries/code lists
I enter "C66729" in the Code lists search area and click "Show" to display the "ROUTE" code list
I see the items in the "ROUTE" code list is displayed
the list has 132 entries
I enter "C38299" in the Code List Items search area and click "Show" to display the "SUBCUTANEOUS" code list item
I see the "SUBCUTANEOUS" code list item
I see that the shared Preferred terms are displayed as "CMROUTE" and "EXROUTE"
I see that the shared Synonyms are displayed as "CMROUTE" and "EXROUTE"
I click "Change instructions" in the context menu (on top left corner of the page)
I see that "No Change Instructions were found."
that it is not possible to add any "change instruction"
I click "close"
click "Home" in the top navigation bar
the Dashbaord is displayed
I click "Browse latest version" button
I see the list of code lists included in the latest release version as specified in pre-condition
